.\" Man page for hs2
.\" Contact chris@hammerspoon.org to correct errors or typos.
.TH hs2 1 "December 2025" "Hammerspoon 2" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
hs2 \- Hammerspoon 2 command line interface
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B hs2
[\fB\-isCqnN\fR]
[\fB\-a\fR \fIarg\fR]
[\fB\-c\fR \fIcode\fR]
[\fB\-m\fR \fIname\fR]
[\fB\-t\fR \fIseconds\fR]
[\fIfile\fR]
[\fB\-\-\fR \fIarguments\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B hs2
is a command-line tool for interacting with Hammerspoon 2, a powerful macOS automation application. It allows you to execute JavaScript code in the Hammerspoon 2 environment, either interactively or from the command line.
.PP
Hammerspoon 2 uses JavaScript (via JavaScriptCore) as its scripting language, providing access to native macOS APIs for window management, application control, hotkey binding, and much more.
.PP
The
.B hs2
tool communicates with a running Hammerspoon 2 instance via IPC (CFMessagePort), allowing you to:
.IP \(bu 2
Execute JavaScript code from the terminal
.IP \(bu 2
Run JavaScript scripts as command-line tools
.IP \(bu 2
Use an interactive REPL for development and testing
.IP \(bu 2
Integrate Hammerspoon 2 automation into shell scripts
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-a " arg"
Pass argument to script. The argument is appended to
.BR _cli.args .
Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
.B \-i
Force interactive mode (REPL). By default, interactive mode is activated when no code, file, or stdin input is provided and stdout is a TTY.
.TP
.B \-s
Read JavaScript code from standard input. This option is automatically enabled when stdin is not a TTY (i.e., when input is piped).
.TP
.BI \-c " code"
Execute the specified JavaScript code. This option can be repeated to execute multiple code snippets in sequence.
.TP
.BI \-m " name"
Connect to a custom IPC message port. Default is "Hammerspoon2". This allows communication with alternative Hammerspoon 2 instances or custom IPC servers.
.TP
.B \-n
Disable colored output. By default, colors are enabled when stdout is a TTY.
.TP
.B \-N
Force colored output, even when stdout is not a TTY.
.TP
.B \-C
Enable console mirroring (not yet functional). When enabled, output from Hammerspoon 2's console (console.log, etc.) will be mirrored to the terminal.
.TP
.B \-q
Quiet mode. Suppresses normal output; only errors are displayed.
.TP
.BI \-t " seconds"
Set the IPC timeout in seconds. Default is 4.0. This affects how long
.B hs2
will wait for responses from Hammerspoon 2.
.TP
.B \-h
Display help information and exit.
.TP
.B \-\-
Stop parsing options. All arguments after
.B \-\-
are available to the JavaScript code via
.BR _cli.args .
.SH EXAMPLES
.SS Execute a simple command
.nf
.RS
hs2 \-c "hs.alert.show('Hello from terminal')"
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SS Start an interactive REPL
.nf
.RS
hs2 \-i
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SS Execute a JavaScript file
.nf
.RS
hs2 ~/scripts/window\-manager.js
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SS Pipe commands to hs2
.nf
.RS
echo "console.log(hs.application.frontmostApplication().title())" | hs2
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SS Execute code with custom arguments
.nf
.RS
hs2 \-c "console.log('Arguments:', _cli.args)" \-\- arg1 arg2 arg3
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SS Use in a shebang script
Create a file
.I automation.js
with:
.nf
.RS
#!/usr/local/bin/hs2
console.log("Running automation script");
hs.application.launchOrFocus("Safari");
.RE
.fi
.PP
Make it executable and run:
.nf
.RS
chmod +x automation.js
./automation.js
.RE
.fi
.PP
.SH INTERACTIVE MODE
When run in interactive mode (REPL),
.B hs2
provides a JavaScript prompt where you can execute code line by line. Features include:
.IP \(bu 2
Command history (in-session via up/down arrows)
.IP \(bu 2
Tab completion for hs.* module names
.PP
To exit the REPL, press
.B Ctrl\-D
or enter
.BR quit() .
.SH SPECIAL VARIABLES
When JavaScript code is executed via
.BR hs2 ,
the following special variables are available:
.TP
.B _cli.remote
A reference to the IPC message port used for communication with Hammerspoon 2.
.TP
.B _cli.quietMode
Boolean indicating whether quiet mode (\-q) is enabled.
.TP
.B _cli.console
Boolean indicating whether console mirroring (\-C) is enabled.
.TP
.B _cli.args
Array of custom arguments passed after
.BR \-\- .
.TP
.B print(...)
Enhanced print function that outputs to the terminal (via IPC) rather than Hammerspoon 2's console.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/Hammerspoon2/init.js
Default Hammerspoon 2 configuration file.
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 64
Invalid command-line arguments.
.TP
.B 65
IPC protocol/communication error.
.TP
.B 66
Error reading input file or stdin.
.TP
.B 69
Hammerspoon 2 not reachable or IPC error.
.TP
.B 75
Temporary failure (e.g., during Hammerspoon 2 startup).
